The /nodes/read API provides a response in the following format:

200 Success

NodeList Model - Contains sets of node lists for each target environment.
BacktestNodes Node Array
Collection of backtest nodes.
LiveNodes Node Array
Collection of live nodes.
ResearchNodes Node Array
Collection of research nodes.
Example 
{
  "BacktestNodes": [
    {
      "Speed": ,
      "Prices": {
        "Monthly": 0,
        "Yearly": 0
      },
      "CpuCount": 0,
      "Ram": ,
      "Name": "string"
    }
  ],
  "LiveNodes": [
    {
      "Speed": ,
      "Prices": {
        "Monthly": 0,
        "Yearly": 0
      },
      "CpuCount": 0,
      "Ram": ,
      "Name": "string"
    }
  ],
  "ResearchNodes": [
    {
      "Speed": ,
      "Prices": {
        "Monthly": 0,
        "Yearly": 0
      },
      "CpuCount": 0,
      "Ram": ,
      "Name": "string"
    }
  ]
}
Node Model - Contains all relevant information on a Node to interact through API endpoints.
Speed float
The nodes cpu clock speed in GHz.
Prices NodePrices object
Node prices from node object.
CpuCount integer
CPU core count of node.
Ram float
Size of RAM in Gigabytes.
Name string
Name of the node.
Example 
{
  "Speed": ,
  "Prices": {
    "Monthly": 0,
    "Yearly": 0
  },
  "CpuCount": 0,
  "Ram": ,
  "Name": "string"
}
NodePrices Model - Node prices from node object.
Monthly integer
The monthly price of the node in US dollars.
Yearly integer
The yearly price of the node in US dollars.
Example 
{
  "Monthly": 0,
  "Yearly": 0
}

401 Authentication Error

UnauthorizedError Model - Unauthorized response from the API. Key is missing, invalid, or timestamp is too old for hash.
www_authenticate string
Header
